words.replaceText: We at Nihilus Co. will be sad to see you go, be we understand. After all, existence isn't for everyone.
You were born strong and healthy! You only very rarely get sick and bounce back within days!
You were born with an average constitution. Sometimes you will get sick with varying degrees of severity but by and large you get by. You may suffer the occasional health complication.

You have a naturally weak body, and are prone to disease. You will get sick more often than your peers and take longer to recover. In addition, you will suffer frequent health complications and bruise like a peach.

You were born immunocompromised, and even a common cold could be fatal to you. You will suffer frequent health complications and have to constantly take precautions against getting ill, lest you risk dying.
You were born able bodied! You have all four limbs and all five senses.*
You have a mild impairment that while annoying, isn't truly debilitating. Something such as needing glasses or hearing aids.
You have what would be considered a serious disability, such as a missing limb or complete loss of a sense.
You have what would be considered a severe disability, such as lower  body paralysis or extreme nerve damage.

Your Human Brain™ brain is composed of matter and thus subject to all of the laws governing matter. Therefore, with perfect knowledge of the laws of nature and all the nuances of your brain, we may perfectly predict your response to any given stimuli. This doctrine therefore dictates that all actions were merely reactions to previous conditions, going back to the first stimuli. Thusly, as stated by Kane (2005), "Our present actions are the necessary consequences of the past and the laws of nature." (p. 24) Your thoughts are not your own, they are merely the î̷ͅn̸͍̋e̴̹̾v̸̛̟i̸̧̿t̸͈̋a̴̢͑b̴̤̚l̸͉̄è̵̡ ̶͐͜c̷̙̎ō̷̘n̴̝̏s̶̯̎e̸̓͜q̷̦̏u̷̫̍e̷̔͜ṋ̴͗c̷̟̏e̶̼̅s̸͈͑ of existence.
This option will grant you a soul from the Abrahamic God. It will allow to go to either heaven or hell when you pass, with your destination depending on your actions.

You have rejected divinity, and embraced quantum mechanics. Quantum uncertainty has set you f̸̪̔r̵̭͗e̸͔͗e̷͂. Your actions cannot be predetermined because they are inherently undetermined until the fateful moment.
You have accepted that none of this matters. We at Nihilus Co. thank you for accepting your f̷͍́ạ̵̋t̴͉̄ę̸̍ and ceasing your f̸̙̈ṷ̴͠t̴̬̓í̴̹l̷̞̔e̷̢͛ ̴̰͘ṙ̶͕é̶̮s̶̲̀i̷̟͊s̶̱͗t̴̺͆ḁ̶̿ń̵̢c̵͉̒ė̸̪.

rows.titleText: We have prepared three different soul options for you to choose from. Please choose whichever pleases you.

objects.title: Divine Soul
objects.wordChangeDeselect: This option will grant you a soul from the Abrahamic God. It will allow to go to either heaven or hell when you pass, with your destination depending on your actions.
objects.wordChangeSelect: It doesn't m̵̮̀ȁ̴̖ẗ̶̻́t̵̮̅è̴͇r̴̲̅. God has seen what was and what will be. Your fate has been written.

objects.title: Quantum Soul
objects.wordChangeDeselect: You have rejected divinity, and embraced quantum mechanics. Quantum uncertainty has set you f̸̪̔r̵̭͗e̸͔͗e̷͂. Your actions cannot be predetermined because they are inherently undetermined until the fateful moment.

They make the choices, and you merely act out the motions like a ḡ̴̰ȍ̷͚o̵̭̓d̷̲̒ ̴͓͒l̵͓̈́i̵̊͜t̴̪̾t̵̳͆l̵̻͌é̵̪ ̶̛̟m̴̳͂e̷̞͆à̸͙ṯ̵̋ ̸̫̇p̷̫̈ú̵̪p̴͑͜p̸̢͠e̸̥͛t̵̥͆.

rows.title: Your Ultimate Fate
rows.titleText: Choose your own fate m̶̝̓ó̴͚ŕ̸͖t̵̿͜ą̸͒ľ̸̖. Although isn't that something of a contradiction? If one has a fate their choice was decided from the start, and there is no real choice to be had.

objects.title: Puppet to Forces Greater Than You
objects.text: You are merely a puppet to forces far beyond you. Perhaps god has  a ṕ̷̙l̸̺̈́a̸̫̕n̷̦̆ for you. Perhaps you choose at the whim of q̶͒ͅu̸̬̽a̶̭͛ǹ̵̢t̶͎͐u̵͉̅m̵͕̕ ̶̈ͅu̸͈͗n̵̯͋c̵̗̎ě̶̥r̵̦̃t̷̩̓a̶̹͗i̴̭̿ņ̶͗ṯ̸͌ỷ̸̝. Perhaps you merely are the product of your antecedent conditions and the laws of nature. It doesn't matter. None of it matters. Nothing you do will matter. It all happens as i̴̪͐t̴͙̔ ̵̹͋w̸̋͜ä̷͉ș̶̊ ̴̭̅w̶̜̏ŕ̸̡i̶̝͂t̶̞͛t̶͚͆e̷̪̚n̴̖͐. You are not making choices, you are having them made for you. You merely believe you are making those choices. In the words of Kane (2005), There is nothing we can now do to change the fact that our present actions occur (p. 24).

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
